# Amazon EKS WorkShop
Here, you go to find the prerequisites needed to start with the workshop.
 
## Install Terraform 
For this workshop we are going to deploy the infrastructure making use of an infrastructure as a code tool such as terraform. 
Please install the 0.11.13 version

> [Terraform v0.11.13 Binaries \| HashiCorp Releases](https://releases.hashicorp.com/terraform/0.11.13/)


## Install AWS CLI
We need the AWS command line interface (AWS CLI) to interact with the AWS resources needed for the workshop
### Install the AWS CLI in Windows
> [Install the AWS CLI on Windows - Using the MSI Installer](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/install-windows.html#install-msi-on-windows)
> [Install the AWS CLI on Windows - Using Python and pip on Windows](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/install-windows.html#awscli-install-windows-pip)
> [Install the AWS CLI on Windows - Executable to Your Command Line Path](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/install-windows.html#awscli-install-windows-path)

### Install the AWS CLI in Linux
>[Install the AWS CLI on Linux](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/install-linux.html)

### Install the AWS CLI in MacOS
>[Install the AWS CLI on macOS - Using the Bundled Installer](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/install-macos.html#install-bundle-macos)
>
>[Install the AWS CLI on macOS - Using pip](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/install-macos.html#awscli-install-osx-pip)

### Install the AWS CLI in a Virtual Environment

>[Install the AWS CLI in a Virtual Environment - AWS Command Line Interface](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/install-virtualenv.html)

### Install the AWS CLI Using the Bundled Installer (Linux, macOS, or Unix)

>[Install the AWS CLI Using the Bundled Installer (Linux, macOS, or Unix) - AWS Command Line Interface](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/install-bundle.html)
